<div class="sub-content-header">Digital Imaging: PMA@CES </div>
<br />

<P>Digital imaging/photography comes into sharp focus at The Venetian. From a specialized show daily, to exhibits to conference sessions to the industry's most notable awards ceremony, the 2012 CES has you covered from all angles. &nbsp; </P>
<P><STRONG><IMG style="MARGIN-TOP: 3px; FLOAT: left; MARGIN-LEFT: 5px" hspace=5 vspace=3 src="/images/content/ces-daily.jpg" width=67 height=84>Digital Imaging Daily:</STRONG> If digital imaging/photography matters to you, then pick up your copy of the official <EM>CES Digital Imaging/Photography Daily </EM>– available on-site at CES. Produced by Photo Industry Reporter, this publication focuses solely on imaging and features show and industry information as well as the latest breaking news.</P>
<P><B><IMG style="FLOAT: right; MARGIN-LEFT: 5px" hspace=5 src="/images/content/PMA-sq-200-pw.jpg" width=113 height=91>PMA @ CES Conference</B>: <A href="http://www.cesweb.org/conferenceprogram/search/results.asp?categoryID=2158 ">Two tracks cover retail strategy and technology trends</A>, giving you a crystal clear picture of opportunities in photo and the future of digital imaging. The sessions are the perfect complement to the exhibits, which feature more than <STRONG><A href="http://ces12.mapyourshow.com/5_0/exhibitor_results.cfm?CFID=30916924&CFTOKEN=b1eca1e4f43ec80b-C26DD5F2-BDC4-CA5C-9A3777C1106309E9&type=pavilion&pavilion=PMA@CES" target=_blank>130 companies – from AAA Imaging to Zear.</A></STRONG>&nbsp;</P>
<P><STRONG>PMDA Awards and After Party</STRONG><BR>7:30 p.m. Monday, January 9<BR>ARIA, Haze Nightclub<BR>The PhotoImaging Manufacturers and Distributors Association (PMDA), the photo industry's preeminent trade organization, will honor&nbsp;six individuals for their outstanding contributions to the imaging industry at their annual <A href="http://cesweb.org/awards/pmda-awards.asp">PMDA Awards Ceremony and after-party</A>. </P>
<P>Honorees include: &nbsp; </P>
<UL>
<LI>Person of the Year: Sir Howard Stringer – chairman, chief executive officer and president, Sony Corporation<IMG style="FLOAT: right" alt="" src="/images/content/PMDA_logo.JPG" width=140 height=95> </LI>
<LI>Visionary Award: Jeffery Housenbold – president and CEO, Shutterfly </LI>
<LI>Lifetime Achievement Award : Mona Kelly – photo and front end consultant </LI>
<LI>Photographer of the Year: Carol Guzy – Pulitzer Prize Winner, The Washington Post </LI>
<LI>Technical Achievement Award: Tatsuo Konno – Canon Inc. </LI>
<LI>PMA/DIMA Lifetime Achievement Award: Dr. George Smith – Nobel Prize in Physics </LI></UL>
<P>Tickets are $200. For more information, or to reserve seating, please contact Michelle Tramantano at <A href="mailto:michelle@pmda.com">michelle@pmda.com</A>.</P><br />
